<subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-forming-quadratic-expressions-in-real-life" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Forming Quadratic Expressions in Real-Life</title>
    <objectives component="outcomes">
        <introduction xml:id="auto_ge1wbvrb">
            <p xml:id="auto_0ir0vi9k">
            <dl>
                <li xml:id="auto_tjbsz48x">
                    <title>Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_ckdq3006">
                        1.0 Numbers and Algebra
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_awi1jm3u">
                    <title>Sub-Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_kg0w2kya">
                        1.3 Quadratic Expressions and Equations
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_f4pw1ja5">
                    <title>Specific Learning Outcomes</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_a3skodde">
                        Form quadratic expressions from different situations
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_xicegmxx" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Grade Level</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_u98t16a8">
                        10
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_xfmvb33n" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Estimated Duration</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_hxo1royw">
                        40 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_2aglv25h" component="lesson-plan">
                <p xml:id="auto_jndexor1"> Upon completion of this lesson, learners will be able to:
                <ol>
                    <li xml:id="auto_feb0sd0d">
                        <p xml:id="auto_tl9x3dg7">
                            <alert>Know (Conceptual Understanding):</alert> Understand how real-life situations involving area, consecutive numbers, and optimization lead to quadratic expressions.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_oexoq0g7">
                        <p xml:id="auto_9cgacpvo">
                            <alert>Do (Procedural Skill):</alert> Form quadratic expressions from real-world contexts by identifying variables, writing expressions, and expanding using the distributive property.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_3ji218i9">
                        <p xml:id="auto_267eacdl">
                            <alert>Apply (Application/Problem-Solving):</alert> Apply quadratic expression formation to model and solve problems involving gardens, number puzzles, and courtyards.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                </p>
            </p>
        </introduction>
    </objectives>
